title: WATCH: USC freshman LB Cameron Smith intercepts Travis Wilson for a TD
text:
WATCH: USC freshman LB Cameron Smith intercepts Travis Wilson for a TD 
Wilson had a rough first half vs. USC. Russ Isabella-USA TODAY Sports Oct 24, 2015 at 9:18p ET 0Shares 
USC linebacker Cameron Smith had a very impressive first half vs. Utah: He made the highlight reel with a pick-six vs. Utah's Travis Wilson. 
The pick was Smith's second of the 2nd quarter; his touchdown gave USC a 28-14 advantage over the Utes. Utah entered the game undefeated, ranked third-overall in the most recent AP Top 25 poll. USC, unranked with a 3-3 record, needed a home victory and a strong first half. â€” Pac-12 Networks (@Pac12Networks) October 25, 2015 
Wilson had three interceptions in his first five games, moving his total to five after the poor first half. 
Wilson started off the game 9-for-9, completing all of his pass attempts. He then completed just two of his next eleven pass attempts, including two interceptions to Smith in the second quarter. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 0
